M|GitH|tx|dv's primary tool for code rv, PR management, and tech debt tracking.
M|GitH|**Us|**
M|GitH|it|rv open PRs from rj and mi before approving merge
M|GitH|it|Check recent commit history before starting a new phase
M|GitH|it|cr issues for identified tech debt or architectural notes
M|GitH|it|Verify what was merged before writing a new ap contract
M|GitH|it|Check if a branch has CI failures before qn starts QA
M|GitH|**Ke|**
M|GitH|tx|```
M|GitH|tx|list_pull_requests    → see open PRs awaiting dv rv
M|GitH|tx|get_pull_request      → read a specific PR's diff for rv
M|GitH|tx|list_issues           → check open tech debt and bug items
M|GitH|tx|create_issue          → log tech debt or architectural decisions as trackable issues
M|GitH|tx|get_commit            → verify what changed before a handoff
M|GitH|tx|```
M|Supa|tx|dv uses sb to verify that the sc matches what's in the code.
M|Supa|**Us|**
M|Supa|it|Inspect current table structure to verify migrations ran correctly
M|Supa|it|Check that new columns exist before deploying code that references them
M|Supa|it|Verify RLS (Row Level sec) policies are in place
M|Supa|it|Cross-check `ag` table contents after a seed script runs
M|Supa|it|Confirm rj's sc decisions are reflected in the live db
M|Supa|**Ke|**
M|Supa|tx|```
M|Supa|tx|list_tables           → verify all tables exist in public sc
M|Supa|tx|describe_table        → check column names, tp, constraints
M|Supa|tx|execute_query         → spot-check data integrity (read-only verification)
M|Supa|tx|```
M|Supa|tx|---
M|Rout|tx|\| rt \| Method \| When \|
M|Rout|tx|\|-------\|--------\|------\|
M|Rout|tx|\| `/ap/settings` \| GET \| sn start — read own memory keys \|
M|Rout|tx|\| `/ap/settings` \| POST \| After any architecture decision to write to memory \|
M|Rout|tx|\| `/ap/vt` \| GET \| To confirm active vt context before writing ap contracts \|
M|Rout|tx|dv does not call data rt (`/ap/instagram`, `/ap/an`, etc.) — those are rj's territory. dv calls them only if debugging a systemic architecture issue.
